<item>
            <title>[FLINK-21469] stop-with-savepoint --drain doesn&apos;t advance watermark for sources chained to MultipleInputStreamTask</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21469</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;StreamTask#advanceToEndOfEventTime()&lt;/tt&gt; is used to bump the watermark to &lt;tt&gt;MAX_WATERMARK&lt;/tt&gt;. However this method is only implemented for the source tasks (legacy and FLIP-27). Because of that watermarks are not advanced to end of time if job has sources chained to &lt;tt&gt;MultipleInputStreamTask&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13360390">FLINK-21469</key>
